007/**
008 * A palette of predefined colors as packed IPT floats, the kind {@link ColorTools} works with.
009 * You can access colors by their constant name, such as {@code OCEAN_BLUE}, by the {@link #NAMED} map using
010 * {@code NAMED.get("Ocean Blue", 0f)}, or by index in the FloatArray called {@link #LIST}. Note that to access a float
011 * color from NAMED, you need to give a default value if the name is not found; {@code 0f} is a good default because it
012 * will not occur in a valid IPT color. You can access the names in a specific order with {@link #NAMES} (which is
013 * alphabetical), {@link #NAMES_BY_HUE} (which is sorted by the hue of the matching color, from red to yellow to blue
014 * (with gray around here) to purple to red again), or {@link #NAMES_BY_LIGHTNESS} (which is sorted by the channelL of
015 * the matching color, from darkest to lightest). Having a name lets you look up the matching color in {@link #NAMED}.
016 * <br>
017 * Created by Tommy Ettinger on 10/13/2020.
018 */
019public class Palette {
020    public static final ObjectFloatOrderedMap<String> NAMED = new ObjectFloatOrderedMap<>(256);
021    public static final FloatList LIST = new FloatList(256);

3109    /**
3110     * All names for colors in this palette, sorted by lightness from black to white. You can fetch the
3111     * corresponding packed float color by looking up a name in {@link #NAMED}.
3112     */
3113    public static final ObjectList<String> NAMES_BY_LIGHTNESS = new ObjectList<>(NAMES);
3114    static {
3115        NAMES_BY_HUE.sort((o1, o2) -> {
3116            final float c1 = NAMED.get(o1), c2 = NAMED.get(o2);
3117            if(ColorTools.alphaInt(c1) < 128) return -10000;
3118            else if(ColorTools.alphaInt(c2) < 128) return 10000;
3119            final float s1 = ColorTools.oklabSaturation(c1), s2 = ColorTools.oklabSaturation(c2);
3120            if(s1 <= 0.05f && s2 > 0.05f)
3121                return -1000;
3122            else if(s1 > 0.05f && s2 <= 0.05f)
3123                return 1000;
3124            else if(s1 <= 0.05f && s2 <= 0.05f)
3125                return (int)Math.signum(ColorTools.channelL(c1) - ColorTools.channelL(c2));
3126            else
3127                return 2 * (int)Math.signum(ColorTools.oklabHue(c1) - ColorTools.oklabHue(c2))
3128                        + (int)Math.signum(ColorTools.channelL(c1) - ColorTools.channelL(c2));
3129        });
3130        NAMES_BY_LIGHTNESS.sort((o1, o2) ->
3131                Float.compare(ColorTools.channelL(NAMED.get(o1)), ColorTools.channelL(NAMED.get(o2))));
